about-title = About
about-intro-1 = Samuel Asher Rivello is a professional game developer with 20+ years of XP across gameplay programming, technical leadership, and production-ready interactive experiences.
about-intro-2 = His work spans Unity, C#, Rust, Dioxus, Bevy, web apps, tools, and game systems that balance player-facing polish with maintainable engineering.
about-intro-3 = He helps teams with senior implementation, architecture cleanup, prototyping, performance work, and practical delivery support.
rust-title = Rust
rust-copy-1 = Rust brings the kind of reliability this project needs: explicit data flow, strong compile-time checks, and predictable performance without giving up modern application ergonomics.
rust-copy-2 = It is a practical fit for shared web and desktop code because the same core behavior can be kept small, testable, and safe across both targets.
dioxus-title = Dioxus
dioxus-copy-1 = Dioxus lets the UI stay in Rust while still feeling like a browser app: components, routes, assets, and styling all live close to the code that uses them.
dioxus-copy-2 = For this token list, that means one shared interface can support the web build and the desktop shell without duplicating the app experience.
